cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DB 

This paper discusses a method for improving the quality of labeled datasets for machine learning applications through the programmatic creation of labels using noisy heuristics. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses incorporating pairwise feedback into the labeling process, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and potentially cybersecurity (cs.CR) if the feedback is generated by humans. Finally, the creation and management of datasets is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB).
